Q: What is a selector?
A selector find a matched set

BASIC SELECTORS
$('p')                      select all paragephs in the doc
$('#some-id')               select a single elemnt with this ID
$('.some-class')            select all elements that have this class
$('img[alt]')               select images with alt attributes

MORE ADVANCED SELECTORS
$('#switcher button')       select all the button in the 'switcher' div
$('#selected-plays > li')   select first level below element with ID  Note: > is child combinator
$('a[href^="mailto:"]')     select all anchor elements with the href attribute that begin with mailto:
$('a[href$=".pdf"]')        select all anchor elements with the href attribute that end with .pdf
$('a[href*="henry"]')       select all anchor elements whose href include the weod henry
$('tr:even')                select alternative rows
$('tr:odd')                 select alternative rows
$('tr:contains(Henry)')     select rows that contain Henry <-- Note: contains is case sensitive!

$('#selected-plays li:not(.horizontal)')    select first level below element and all list element not part of horizontal class
$('a[href*="henry"][href^=http:"]')         select all anchor elements with those 2 href attribute conditions
$('div.horizontal:eq(1)')                   select SECOND child of div with horizontal class (JS array are 0 based)
$('div.first-child')                        select FIRST child of
$('div.nth-child(1)')                       select FIRST child of
$('div.nth-child(odd)')                     select FIRST child of

FORM SELECTORS
:input  
:button
:enabled
:disabled
:checked
:selected
$('input[type="radio"]:checked')           select all checked radio buttons

COMPOUND SELECT
$('input[type="password"],input[type="text"]:disabled')     select password input and disabled lineedit


FILTER-BASED SELECTORS
CUSTOM SELECTORS

$('tr').filter('even')                                              is equivalent to $('tr:even')
$('a').filter (function() {                                         is for custom selector
    return this.hostname && this.hostname != location.hostname;     <-- location.hostname = hostname of current page
}).addClass('external');

SELECTORS + FUNCTION

$('td:contains(Henry)').next()                  select only the sibling after the matched element
$('td:contains(Henry)').nextAll()               select only all the siblings after the matched element
$('td:contains(Henry)').nextAll().andSelf()     select matched element and all its siblings
$('td:contains(Henry)').parent().children()     select matched element and all its siblings
$('td:contains(Henry)').parent().children()[3]  select 3rd siblings

$('td:contains(Henry)').parent().find('td:eq(1)').addClass(...)end().find('tr:eq(2)').addClass(...)

